Package: simFastBOIN
Type: Package
Title: Fast Bayesian Optimal Interval Design for Phase I Dose-Finding Trials
Version: 1.3.0
Date: 2024-12-06
Authors@R: person(given = "Gosuke",
                  family = "Homma",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "my.name.is.gosuke@gmail.com",
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6854-5627"))
Description: 
    Fast and efficient simulation tools for Bayesian Optimal Interval (BOIN) 
    designs in Phase I clinical trials. Provides functions for conducting trial 
    simulations, evaluating operating characteristics across multiple scenarios, 
    and generating publication-ready tables. The package uses vectorized operations 
    and C-based isotonic regression (via Iso::pava()) to achieve superior performance 
    while maintaining full compatibility with BOIN methodology. Results match the 
    BOIN package within 0.5% across all scenarios. Version 1.3.0 adds progress 
    message control (verbose parameter) for clean output in reports and vignettes. 
    Version 1.2.1 introduced multi-scenario simulations and HTML table formatting. 
    Version 1.2.0 restored exact BOIN compatibility and updated default parameters. 
    Version 1.1.0 added conservative MTD selection (boundMTD) and flexible early 
    stopping rules (n_earlystop_rule). Reference: Liu and Yuan (2015) 
    <doi:10.1111/rssc.12089>.
